The paper deals with data structures for the membership problem, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The use of expanders and probabilistic bit-probe schemes suggests that the paper belongs to the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also deals with the analysis of space complexity, which is a common theme in computational complexity (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of graphs and expanders suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of computational geometry (cs.CG) or numerical analysis (cs.NA).
